U.S. Treasury Department Schedule for Thursday, March 10

-- B y   V i n c e n t   D e l   G i u d i c e
-- 
2011-03-10T13:25:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-10/u-s-treasury-department-schedule-for-thursday-march-10.html
The following is a reformatted
version of the U.S. Treasury Department’s daily release on the
schedule for Secretary Timothy F. Geithner and other officials:  On Thursday morning, Secretary Geithner will meet with
members of the  Business Roundtable  for a private discussion on
the Administration’s agenda for promoting  job creation , economic
growth and the competitiveness of U.S. firms. This meeting is
closed press.  On Thursday afternoon, Deputy Secretary Wolin will
participate in a panel session entitled “Cyber-Security for the
Financial Sector and the Nation” at the Financial Services
Roundtable 2011 Spring Meeting. The panel will discuss the
nature of national cyber security concerns and plans for
enhancing the government’s cyber-security collaboration with the
private sector. This event is closed press.  In the afternoon, the Secretary will meet with the
President at the White House. This meeting is closed press.  Later, Secretary Geithner will meet with Representative
Serrano on Capitol Hill. This meeting is closed press.  In the evening, the Secretary will host business leaders at
Treasury for a discussion on the state of the economy, industry
and employment trends and corporate  tax reform . This meeting is
closed press.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vincent Del Giudice in  Washington  
 vdelgiudice@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Wellisz at   cwellisz@bloomberg.net  